claim: Flublok is produced using a novel production platform in which recombinant HA is expressed in insect cells using a baculovirus expression vector system (BEVS).
explanation: A table showing vaccine effectiveness (VE, % with 95% CI) of various influenza vaccines, including recombinant quadrivalent influenza vaccine (RIV4), standard dose quadrivalent influenza vaccine (SD-IIV4), RIV4 + high dose quadrivalent influenza vaccine (HD-IIV4) + adjuvanted influenza vaccine (Adj-IV), stratified by age groups (18–64 years and ≥65 years). The table presents clinical vaccine effectiveness data and does not include any information on production platform or expression system, therefore it does not support the claim. Note: The image is clear but focuses solely on effectiveness data; production details are not addressed.
